adjectives.description: unpretty (comparative more unpretty, superlative most unpretty)

examples: I wish I could tie you up in my shoes, / Make you feel unpretty too. / I was told I was beautiful / But what does that mean to you?

verbs.description: unpretty (third-person singular simple present unpretties, present participle unprettying, simple past and past participle unprettied)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To make unpretty or less attractive
examples: Vast gloom unprettied the features of Herman Ruth today when he gave himself to serious contemplation of the distressing futility of many things and how increasingly tough it's becoming for an honest feller to get along in this wearying world.
